'''Irving Domingo Lorenzo Jr.''' (June 26, 1970 – February 5, 2025), professionally known as '''Irv Gotti''' or '''DJ Irv''', was an American record producer. He co-founded the record label [[Murder Inc. Records]] in 1998, which was an imprint of [[Def Jam Recordings]]. Irv is credited with having helped discover or sign rappers [[Jay-Z]], [[DMX]], and [[Ja Rule]], as well as singers [[Ashanti (singer)|Ashanti]] and [[Lloyd (singer)|Lloyd]]. He executively produced the debut albums for DMX's ''[[It's Dark and Hell Is Hot]]'', Ja Rule's ''[[Venni Vetti Vecci]]'', Ashanti's ''[[Ashanti (album)|self titled]]'', and Lloyd's ''[[Southside (Lloyd album)|Southside]]''.<ref name="p775">{{cite web | last=Rashbaum | first=William K. | last2=Sweeney | first2=Matthew | title=Hip-Hop Producers Get Acquittal, Then Hugs, From Jurors | website=The New York Times | date=2005-12-03 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/12/03/nyregion/hiphop-producers-get-acquittal-then-hugs-from-jurors.html | access-date=2025-02-06}}</ref><ref name="d643">{{cite web | last=Dolech | first=Marc W. | title=Irv Gotti's Office Raided | website=Rolling Stone | date=2003-01-06 | url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/irv-gottis-office-raided-185149/ | access-date=2025-02-06}}</ref><ref name="x101">{{cite web | last=Savage | first=Mark | title=Irv Gotti, who created hits for Jennifer Lopez and Ja Rule, dies at 54 | website=BBC Home | date=2025-02-06 | url=https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c5y208g5l5yo | access-date=2025-02-06}}</ref><ref name="g829">{{cite web | last=Jones | first=Alexandra Mae | title=Irv Gotti, hip-hop producer and co-founder of Murder, Inc., dead at 54 | website=CBC | date=2025-02-06 | url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/irv-gotti-obit-1.7452261 | access-date=2025-02-10}}</ref>

Irv received production credits for most of the recordings by artists signed to the label—including Ja Rule (''[[Rule 3:36]]'', ''[[Pain Is Love]]'', ''[[The Last Temptation (Ja Rule album)|The Last Temptation]]'', ''[[R.U.L.E.]]''), [[Murder Inc. Records|The Inc.]] (''[[Irv Gotti Presents: The Inc.]]''), Ashanti (''[[Chapter II (Ashanti album)|Chapter II]]'', ''[[Concrete Rose]]''), and Lloyd (''[[Street Love]]'')—as well as singles for other artists such as [[Jennifer Lopez]] (''[[I'm Real (Jennifer Lopez song)|I'm Real (Murder Remix]])'', ''[[Ain't It Funny (Murder Remix)]]''), [[Fat Joe]] (''[[What's Luv]]''), [[Eve (rapper)|Eve]] (''[[Gangsta Lovin']]''), and [[Kanye West]] (''[[Violent Crimes (song)|Violent Crimes]]''), among others. Gotti was also the creator of the [[BET]] series ''[[Tales (TV series)|Tales]]''.

== Early life ==
Irving Domingo Lorenzo Jr. was born in the [[Hollis, Queens|Hollis]] neighborhood of [[Queens]], [[New York City]], on June 26, 1970.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/irv-gotti-mn0000773161/biography|title = Irv Gotti Biography, Songs, & Albums|website = [[AllMusic]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=January 22, 2012 |title=Irv Gotti To Def Jam: "[They] Ain't F*cking W/ Me, I'm Too Much Of A N*gga" [Video] &#124; SOHH.COM |url=http://www.sohh.com/2012/01/def_jam_aint_fcking_w_me_im_too_much_of.html |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122224008/http://www.sohh.com/2012/01/def_jam_aint_fcking_w_me_im_too_much_of.html |archive-date=January 22, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thesmokinggun.com/archive/1008041hiphop23.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041012012800/http://www.thesmokinggun.com/archive/1008041hiphop23.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=October 12, 2004 |title=The Smoking Gun: Archive |date=October 12, 2004}}</ref> Lorenzo was of [[Filipinos|Filipino]] descent from his paternal grandfather<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Beg5c4hnpDT/?hl=en|title=My Dad's Dad!! My Grandfather. Where my Family gets that flavor from. He Passed Away before I got to know him... |website=Instagram.com|access-date=February 6, 2025}}</ref> and of [[African-American]] descent. His father Irving was a taxicab driver. He had six siblings, including two sisters and an older brother named Chris

