'''Dennis Schröder''' ({{IPA|de|ˈdɛnɪs ˈʃʁøːdɐ}}; born 15 September 1993)<ref name=timur>{{cite web|first=Timur|last=Tinç|title=Im Namen des Vaters|url=https://www.fr.de/sport/sport-mix/namen-vaters-11274268.html|website=fr.de|date=19 January 2019|access-date=22 August 2023|language=de}}</ref> is a German professional [[basketball player]] for the [[Detroit Pistons]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA). He previously played for [[SG Braunschweig]] and [[Phantoms Braunschweig]] in Germany, before joining the [[Atlanta Hawks]] for his first five seasons in the NBA. He is the sole owner of his German hometown team, [[Basketball Löwen Braunschweig|Basketball Loewen Braunschweig]] of the [[Basketball Bundesliga]], and had been the majority shareholder of the team since 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dennis Schroder becomes sole owner of hometown club Braunschweig|url=https://www.eurohoops.net/en/bbl/1062140/dennis-schroder-becomes-the-sole-owner-of-hometown-club-braunschweig/|website=EuroHoops.net|date=22 May 2020|access-date=22 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Nick|last=Crain|title=OKC Thunder's Dennis Schroder Invests In His Former German Professional Team|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/nicholascrain/2020/05/21/okc-thunders-dennis-schroder-invests-in-his-former-german-professional-team/|website=Forbes|date=21 May 2020|access-date=22 May 2020}}</ref>

Debuting for the [[Germany men's national basketball team|German national team]] in 2014, Schröder helped the team to its first major medal in 17 years when Germany won bronze at the [[EuroBasket 2022|2022 EuroBasket]]. In 2023, he led the national team to their first [[FIBA Basketball World Cup|World Cup]] title at the [[2023 FIBA Basketball World Cup]] while being named the [[FIBA World Cup MVP]]. The following year, Schröder was the flag bearer for Germany along with [[judo]]ka [[Anna-Maria Wagner]] at [[2024 Summer Olympics|2024 Summer Olympics in Paris]].<ref name="Aussiedlerbote.com">{{cite web|url=https://aussiedlerbote.de/en/statement-schroder-and-wagner-carry-the-flag-in-paris/|title=Statement: Schröder and Wagner carry the flag in Paris|publisher=Aussiedlerbote.com|language=EN|date=July 23, 2024|access-date=July 23, 2024}}</ref> He helped Germany to a fourth place finish and was named to the [[FIBA Men's Olympics All-Star Five|FIBA Olympics All-Star Five team]].

